##########################################
# To run
##########################################
To run the program, run ./RunMe and follow the prompts.

For each corpus, ./RunMe creates six sonnets, one for 
each possible combination of the different methods used
to create the sonnets
	-Generation: HMM v. Markov model
	-Semantics: First-line, first-seed v. Best-line, first-seed v. best-line, best-seed

Note: due to a very rare library bug, occasionally the script may fail. 
If this occurs please just rerun the script.

##########################################
# File organization
##########################################
Markov Models: markov.py, hmm.py
HTML processing: process_html.py, process_html2.py
Corpora preprocessing: shakespeare.py, process_corpus.py
Semantics: sonnet.py
Modified Proununciation dictionary: pronunciation.txt
